{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"9.3 (part 3) execution plan — refined after grimp SCC analysis in worktree janitor/item-9.3-facade-reads:\n\nFINDING: rebar._reads is ITSELF in the 36-module SCC. Its only ->rebar (facade) back-edge is the lazy 'from rebar import RebarError' (line 45); 'from rebar import config' is a submodule edge (->rebar.config, a leaf) and does NOT bind it to the facade. So the measurable cycle win comes from making _reads a true leaf.\n\nPLAN:\n1. New stdlib-only leaf src/rebar/_errors.py defining RebarError + ConcurrencyError (moved verbatim). __init__.py re-exports them ('from rebar._errors import ...') for full back-compat (rebar.RebarError / from rebar import RebarError unchanged).\n2. _reads.py line 45 imports RebarError from the leaf -> _reads leaves the SCC. Verified via grimp simulation: largest SCC 36 -> 35, _reads removed; import-cycle baseline ratchets down.\n3. Reroute each function-local 'import rebar' read site whose rebar.* calls are ALL exported by _reads (show_ticket/list_tickets/deps/ready/next_batch/search/recent_session_logs) to 'from rebar import _reads': spec_scan, operations, pass1, orchestrator, gate_ops fully drop 'import rebar'; completion/attest/pai_tools/steps reroute their pure-read function scopes and keep 'import rebar' only where the same scope also does writes (comment/tag/edit) or reads not in _reads (verify_signature/get_file_impact). Behavior identical.\n4. scripts/check_import_cycles.py --update to ratchet the baseline; full suite + make lint/mypy green.\n\nNOTE: the big 36->18 collapse would need routing WRITES through a leaf too — out of scope for a reads-only ticket; not attempted here."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783104031940390001,"uuid":"83793a89-a51a-4c97-9497-3760155cbeef"}